narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This course improved my writing skills and prepared me for further English academic writing.
I learned how to structure an academic paper and use the appropriate bibliography. I also learned how to close read a text and discuss its main points
How to craft an argumentative essay and research paper, more insight into the much-debated subject of free speech.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths:
The professor provided many scholarly articles from the different time periods for this class and it is a great way for me to know more about the freedom of speech in different time periods. The professor also provided feedbacks to assignments and essays that improved my learning.
This course was really well organized. We had a little time though for each paper (given it is a summer course)
I enjoyed the fast-paced discussions, the class did not get "stuck" in any one topic, the subject matter was also very interesting to me.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would definitely recommend this course to other students. This course provides me a platform for critical thinking and expresses my own thoughts and opinions.
This class is an excellent choice to get confident with your writing skills
I would, I took it over the summer, but I am sure that I would have had just as good an experience during the regular semester.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
